@@pGRAND MAGI@@W

Grand Magi are the apex synthesis of @@pSorcerer@@W breadth and @@WWizard@@W
precision: arcane generals who command fire, storm, tide, and stone as a
single disciplined doctrine. Where lesser casters specialize, Grand Magi
layer elemental pressure to dominate long fights.

To become a Grand Magi, you follow the adept path tied to @@pSorcerer@@W and
@@WWizard@@W remort progression.

@@pPassive class advantages@@W
Grand Magi gains passive scaling through adept levels:

  1) @@wRemort/Adept non-physical spell damage bonus@@W
     - Non-physical remort/adept damage effects gain a passive Grand Magi
       multiplier.
     - Scaling: +2% damage per Grand Magi adept level (up to +40% at 20).

@@pUnique Grand Magi mechanics@@W
  * @@wMagi stance@@W is available on the adept path and carries caster-focused
    stance flags (either-class access, multi-cast support, dual-cast support,
    and no-hit casting posture).
  * Grand Magi gains a dedicated elemental spell ladder:
      - @@wElemental Inferno@@W (level 1)
      - @@wElemental Shock@@W (level 5)
      - @@wElemental Deluge@@W (level 10)
      - @@wElemental Rupture@@W (level 15)
  * Grand Magi uses @@wIntelligence@@W as its adept prime attribute and follows
    a high-mana caster growth profile.

@@pGrand Magi reincarnation bonuses@@W
Each Grand Magi adept reincarnation grants additional passive scaling:

  * @@wElemental realm damage@@W (fire/air/water/earth): +2% per Grand Magi
    adept reincarnation.

In short: Grand Magi is the sustained elemental adept, turning advanced arcane
progression into consistent, scaling spell pressure across elemental domains.

